The paper deals with the Ingleton-LP bound, which is a concept in information theory and network coding. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves polyhedral cones and half-spaces, which are concepts in computational geometry, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves optimization and linear programming, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of linear network codes, which is a concept in computer networks, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) a possible sub-category.
